<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-063-111 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 262 421</DOCID><JOURNAL>InfoWorld  Sept 9 1991 v13 n36 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>IBM, Apple to form second subsidiary.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Scannell, Ed; Quinlan, Tom.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Apple Computer Inc and IBM will form a second subsidiary, this oneto develop software, hardware and multimedia services.andP;  The twocorporations already have a subsidiary working together ondeveloping a reduced-instruction-set computer workstation andoperating system.andP;  Products from the new subsidiary are expectedto reach the market first.andP;  The new subsidiary's first projectwill be to work on a hand-held computer with a CD-ROM drive,code-named 'Sweet Pea' by Apple.andP;  The new subsidiary will alsodevelop a source-code-level multimedia authoring language.andP;  Thenew subsidiary will also work on Apple's P3-TV multimedia project,which will allow users to download information services, movies,music and videos to a computer or television using a standardtelevision broadcasting medium.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   International Business Machines Corp. (Management)Apple Computer Inc. (Management).andO;Ticker:    AAPL; IBM.andO;Topic:     Subsidiary CompaniesProduct DevelopmentHand-Held ComputersComputer industryMultimedia technology.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>